-- Brazil to ‘Try to Maintain’ Currency at 1.80 Real, O Estado Says
-- B y   M a r i a   L u i z a   R a b e l l o
-- 2012-04-08T13:35:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-08/brazil-to-try-to-maintain-currency-at-1-80-real-o-estado-says.html
Brazil Finance Minister  Guido Mantega  signaled the government “will try to maintain” the
currency at about 1.80 real per dollar, O Estado de S.Paulo
newspaper reported, citing an  interview  with Trade Minister
Fernando Pimentel.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maria Luiza Rabello in Brasilia newsroom at   mrabello@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at  jgoodman19@bloomberg.net 
